HEADWORD: Empyema
<hw>Em`py*e"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<?/, from <?/ to suppurate; <?/ in + <?/ pus.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>A collection of blood, pus, or other fluid, in some cavity of the
body, especially that of the pleura.</def>
<rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The term <xex>empyema</xex> is now restricted to a
collection of pus in the cavity of the pleura.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

